<!--
This single-file portfolio is placed in the canvas as `index.html`.

What this file contains:
- A responsive single-page portfolio built with modern HTML & CSS (no frameworks).
- Sections: Hero, About, Projects, Skills, Experience, Contact, Footer.
- Placeholder project cards you can replace with your own projects and links.
- Comments inside the file explain how to customize, add your resume, and deploy to GitHub Pages.

Files you should add to the same repo (suggested):
- README.md  -> describe yourself and highlight main projects (I can generate this for you)
- resume.pdf -> link to from the site
- /projects/<project-folder> -> each project's README, screenshots, and demo link

Basic git & GitHub steps to publish with GitHub Pages (paste in terminal):
  git init
  git add .
  git commit -m "Initial portfolio"
  git branch -M main
  git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
  git push -u origin main

Then enable GitHub Pages in the repo Settings -> Pages -> Source -> Deploy from branch -> main (/root).

Want me to customize this page with your real bio, projects, and colors? Reply with the details and I will update.
-->

